items.title: Awesome Esp
items.content_text:
### Firmware

*   [MongooseOS (⭐2.6k)](https://github.com/cesanta/mongoose-os) - An IoT specific firmware, with both C and JS. Available for the ESP32/8266.

### Tools

*   [ESPTool-ck (⭐370)](https://github.com/igrr/esptool-ck) - A CLI tool for flashing in the ESP8266.
*   [ESPTool-gui (⭐197)](https://github.com/Rodmg/esptool-gui) - A flashing GUI tool based on ESPTool-ck.
*   [LuaNode (⭐1.2k)](https://github.com/Nicholas3388/LuaNode) - A lua-only SDK for 32/8266.

### Projects / Smart Home and IoT

*   [OpenMQTTGateway (⭐3.8k)](https://github.com/1technophile/OpenMQTTGateway) - An implementation of a multiprotocol MQTT gateway for both ESP's among other devices.
*   [ESPHome](https://esphome.io/) - A full-featured system for controlling ESP's through simple yet powerful configuration files and Home Automation systems.
*   [Sonoff-Homekit (⭐1k)](https://github.com/Gruppio/Sonoff-Homekit) - An alternative firmware for Sonoff devices (and other 8266 devices) which allows control through Apple's Homekit.
*   [EPaperWeatherDisplay (⭐155)](https://github.com/henri98/esp32-e-paper-weatherdisplay) - A very cute e-ink weather display using the ESP32.
*   [SuperGreenOS (⭐193)](https://github.com/supergreenlab/SuperGreenOS) - A full-featured home farming automation software for the ESP32.

### Projects / InfoSec

*   [ESP32-BLECollector (⭐323)](https://github.com/tobozo/ESP32-BLECollector) - A wardriving device which displays BLE devices and collects data from them, all in a nice screen interface.
*   [ArduinoPcap (⭐442)](https://github.com/spacehuhn/ArduinoPcap) - A library which allows generation of .pcap files with network traffic, for both ESP's.
*   [WiFi Satellite](https://hackaday.io/project/28831-wifi-satellite-34c3) - A giant Wifi "satellite" that can monitor all 14 2.4Ghz channels using, well, 14 ESP32s.
*   [ESP8266 Deauther (⭐14k)](https://github.com/spacehuhn/esp8266_deauther) - A very cool pseudojammer (deauther) of Wifi networks that uses the ESP8266.
*   [PacketMonitor (⭐379)](https://github.com/spacehuhn/PacketMonitor32) - A beautiful OLED monitor for packet activity in a WiFi channel. Two versions for each ESP.
*   [WiFiDuck (⭐2.3k)](https://github.com/spacehuhn/WiFiDuck) - A wireless-enabled keystroke injector, analogous, but even more awesome than the Rubber Ducky.
*   [ESP8266 Beacon Spam (⭐1.1k)](https://github.com/spacehuhn/esp8266_beaconSpam) - Want to confuse people? This device creates hundreds of fake WiFi networks.
*   [DeauthDetector (⭐861)](https://github.com/spacehuhn/DeauthDetector) - A small device that shines a light if it detects a WiFi deauth attack. Made by the same guy as the last six projects.

### Projects / Biomedical

*   [HeartyPatch](https://heartypatch.protocentral.com/) - A wearable BLE and WiFi connected ECG-HR patch which uses the ESP32.
*   [HealthyPi v4](https://www.crowdsupply.com/protocentral/healthypi-v4-unplugged) - An amazing open source vital signs monitor that can monitor ECG, respiration, pulse oximetry and body temperature, all run by an ESP32.

### Projects / Others

*   [SoftRF (⭐882)](https://github.com/lyusupov/SoftRF) - A DIY aviation proximity awareness system that can be used in UAV projects.
*   [Retro ESP32 (⭐648)](https://github.com/retro-esp32/RetroESP32) - An extremely cool launcher for the Odroid Go (with the ESP32), which allows emulating several retro consoles.
*   [DroneBridge (⭐532)](https://github.com/DroneBridge/ESP32) - An implementation of DroneBridge, a signal link for drones and UAV's on the ESP32.

### Libraries / Others

*   [Wasm3 (⭐7.6k)](https://github.com/wasm3/wasm3) - A lightning fast WebAssembly interpreter designed for embedded devices, compatible with both ESP's.
*   [ESP-Dash (⭐1k)](https://github.com/ayushsharma82/ESP-DASH) - Beautiful and fast framework for creating remote dashboards in the 8266/32. No internet required.
*   [GUIslice (⭐1.3k)](https://github.com/ImpulseAdventure/GUIslice) - A drag and drop GUI framework for several devices and screen controllers. Compatible with 8266 and 32.
*   [MicroWebSrv2 (⭐685)](https://github.com/jczic/MicroWebSrv2) - A very powerful MicroPython web server which can be used in the ESP32.
*   [TTS (⭐205)](https://github.com/jscrane/TTS) - A somehow good text to speech library for several Arduino devices, both ESP's included.
*   [Koyn (⭐66)](https://github.com/elkrem/koyn) - A decentralized Bitcoin library for the ESP32 and the ESP8266.
*   [UTFT-ESP (⭐91)](https://github.com/gnulabis/UTFT-ESP) - UTFT Support for the ESP32/8266.
*   [TinyGSM (⭐2.1k)](https://github.com/vshymanskyy/TinyGSM) - A quick and simple Arduino library for interaction with GSM modules which can also control the 8266 through AT commands.
*   [mJS (⭐2k)](https://github.com/cesanta/mjs) - A lightweight and restricted JS engine that is used by MongooseOS, compatible on the 32 and 8266.
*   [ESPUI (⭐1k)](https://github.com/s00500/ESPUI) - A simply library for making interactive web interfaces for both ESP's.
*   [ESP32 ePaper (⭐232)](https://github.com/loboris/ESP32_ePaper_example) - A full-featured library for using ePaper modules with the ESP32.
*   [TinyUPnP (⭐106)](https://github.com/ofekp/TinyUPnP) - A lightweight UPnP IGD library for automatic port forwarding on the 8266 and 32.
*   [Esp32SSHClient (⭐47)](https://github.com/J-Rios/Arduino-esp32sshclient) - A library that implements a SSH client in the ESP32.
